About the job
We have just partnered with a well-funded Series A start up seeking a skilled and motivated Cloud Native Software Engineer to join their exceptionally talented team. Your expertise in Kubernetes, Docker, and Golang will be instrumental in driving their backend engineering efforts.


Responsibilities:
Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams to design and enhance our cloud-native platform, leveraging Kubernetes, Docker, and Golang.
Develop scalable and efficient backend solutions for application deployment, management, and orchestration.
Optimize containerization strategies to ensure high performance, scalability, and resource utilization.
Troubleshoot and resolve complex issues related to cloud-native environments, ensuring seamless operation of our platform.
Stay up to date with the latest advancements and best practices in cloud-native software engineering and contribute your knowledge to improve our platform.
Mentor and guide junior engineers, conducting code reviews and promoting engineering best practices.


Requirements:
Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field.
Proven experience as a Software Engineer, Backend Engineer, or similar role.
Strong expertise in Kubernetes, Docker, and Golang, with a focus on backend development.
Experience with eBPF (extended Berkeley Packet Filter) and its integration within cloud-native environments is a strong plus.
Solid understanding of microservices architecture and cloud-native application development principles.
Familiarity with cloud platforms like AWS or Google Cloud Platform and their container services.
Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to troubleshoot complex issues in cloud-native environments.
Strong communication and collaboration skills, enabling effective teamwork within a dynamic environment.
